    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="728"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Williams</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1895.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1119.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 2543, of the 27th ultimo,
                    inclosing a letter and draft which you were requested to deliver to Mr. Julio
                    Sanguily, has been received.</p>
                <p>Your action in not delivering the letter is approved, and Messrs. Teodoro Perez
                    &amp; Co. have been so informed. It would seem, however, that with the knowledge
                    and assent of the authorities, you could hand the proceeds of the draft to Mr.
                    Sanguily with a statement of the source from which it comes. The draft is
                    returned to you for delivery in accordance with the above suggestion.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
